{"name": "python-datauri", "metadata": {"name": "python-datauri", "version": "3.0.0", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 4 - Beta", "License :: OSI Approved :: The Unlicense (Unlicense)", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9"], "home_page": "https://github.com/fcurella/python-datauri/", "license": "Unlicense", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["typing_extensions"], "summary": "A li'l class for data URI manipulation in Python", "upload_time": 1732727492}, "documentation": ["# DataURI\n\n```{image} https://github.com/fcurella/python-datauri/workflows/Python%20Tests/badge.svg\n:alt: Build status of the master branch on Mac/Linux\n:target: https://github.com/fcurella/python-datauri/actions?query=workflow%3A%22Python+Tests%22\n```\n\n```{image} https://coveralls.io/repos/github/fcurella/python-datauri/badge.svg?branch=master\n:target: https://coveralls.io/github/fcurella/python-datauri?branch=master\n```\n\nData URI manipulation made easy.\n\nThis isn't very robust, and will reject a number of valid data URIs. However, it meets the most useful case: a mimetype, a charset, and the base64 flag.\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\n$ pip install python-datauri\n```\n\n## Parsing\n\n```python\n>>> from datauri import DataURI\n>>> uri = DataURI('data:text/plain;charset=utf-8;base64,VGhlIHF1aWNrIGJyb3duIGZveCBqdW1wZWQgb3ZlciB0aGUgbGF6eSBkb2cu')\n>>> uri.mimetype\n'text/plain'\n>>> uri.charset\n'utf-8'\n>>> uri.is_base64\nTrue\n>>> uri.data\nb'The quick brown fox jumped over the lazy dog.'\n```\n\nNote that `DataURI.data` will always return bytes.\nUse `DataURI.text` to get a string.\n\n## Creating from a string\n\n```python\n>>> from datauri import DataURI\n>>> made = DataURI.make('text/plain', charset='us-ascii', base64=True, data='This is a message.')\n>>> made\nDataURI('data:text/plain;charset=us-ascii;base64,VGhpcyBpcyBhIG1lc3NhZ2Uu')\n>>> made.data\nb'This is a message.'\n```\n\n## Creating from a file\n\nThis is really just a convenience method.\n\n```python\n>>> from datauri import DataURI\n>>> png_uri = DataURI.from_file('somefile.png')\n>>> png_uri.mimetype\n'image/png'\n>>> png_uri.data\nb'\\x89PNG\\r\\n...'\n```\n\n## Serializing\n\n`DataURI` is a subclass of `str`, so you can just use `str()` to print it out:\n\n```python\n>>> from datauri import DataURI\n>>> png_uri = DataURI.from_file('somefile.png')\n>>> str(png_uri)\n'data:image/jpeg;base64,/9j/4AAQSkZJRgABAQAASABIA...'\n```\n\n## Pydantic Support\n\nYou can use `DataURI` as a type for `Pydantic`:\n\n```python\nfrom datauri import DataURI\nfrom pydantic import BaseModel\n\n\nclass ProfilePicture(BaseModel):\n  image_data: DataURI\n```\n\n## License\n\nThis code is released under the [Unlicense](http://unlicense.org/).\n\n## Credits\n\nThis is a repackaging of [this Gist](https://gist.github.com/zacharyvoase/5538178)\noriginally written by [Zachary Voase](https://github.com/zacharyvoase).\n"], "modules": [{"name": "datauri.exceptions", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "datauri.exceptions.InvalidMimeType", "bases": ["ValueError"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "datauri.exceptions.InvalidCharset", "bases": ["ValueError"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "datauri.exceptions.InvalidDataURI", "bases": ["ValueError"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "datauri", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "datauri.T", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "datauri.MIMETYPE_REGEX", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "datauri._MIMETYPE_RE", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "datauri.CHARSET_REGEX", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "datauri._CHARSET_RE", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "datauri.DATA_URI_REGEX", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "datauri._DATA_URI_RE", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "datauri.DataURI", "bases": ["str"], "methods": [{"name": "datauri.DataURI.make", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cls", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "mimetype", "type": {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}, {"name": "charset", "type": {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}, {"name": "base64", "type": {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}, {"name": "data", "type": {"name": "Union", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Union", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "bytes", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bytes", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "Self", "xref": {"fqname": "typing_extensions.Self", "project": "typing-extensions"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "datauri.DataURI.from_file", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cls", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "filename", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "charset", "type": {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typin